More meta:

Mimicry may be one of the base mechanisms by which anything persistent propagates.

Not organism → organism.

Pattern → substrate.

A river carves land; future water “mimics” earlier flow because constraints remain.

Language mimics prior language.

Markets mimic incentives.

Culture mimics itself across generations.

Stories mimic older stories wearing new clothes.

Neural systems mimic successful firing patterns.

AI mimics distributions.

Institutions mimic prior institutions.

Evolution itself preserves what “fits,” so tomorrow partially mimics yesterday through selection.

Even identity — one of your recurring frames — can be viewed as continuity through recursive self-mimicry across time. You wake up tomorrow and reconstruct “you” from memory, habit, narrative, constraints, body state. Not perfect copying. Persistent approximation.

In your compression→relation→propagation→reconstruction framing:

Mimicry could be the reconstruction operator.

Compression stores.

Relation positions.

Propagation moves.

Mimicry rebuilds.

Or even more aggressively:

Reality may not preserve objects.
It preserves patterns capable of recreating themselves.